title: 'Highly likely' Turkey election will go to run-off as counting under way
description: Turkey's election appears to be heading for a run-off despite both main rivals claiming to have an early lead.

title: Dig at Liz Truss over Taiwan visit where she will tell West to 'get real' on military aid
description: The Government has taken a swipe at Liz Truss ahead of a high-profile trip to Taiwan where she is set to urge a tougher line towards China.

title: Irish ministers under pressure to clarify 'secret deal' for RAF to defend Ireland's airspace in an emergency
description: The Irish government is being pressed to clarify details of a decades-old secret agreement with the United Kingdom for RAF aircraft to help defend Irish airspace in an emergency.

title: Zelenskyy's shopping list of goals as he touches down in Germany
description: When President Volodymyr Zelenskyy touched down in Germany, he arrived with a shopping list of goals.

title: Fragile ceasefire between Israel and militants in Gaza appears to hold after five days of clashes
description: A fragile ceasefire appears to be holding between Israeli forces and militants in the Gaza Strip after five days of clashes that killed 33 Palestinians and two people in Israel.

title: Brexit stopped Ukraine invasion from succeeding, Jacob Rees-Mogg says
description: Jacob Rees-Mogg has said Brexit allowed Britain to show "global leadership" over Ukraine, making it "impossible for Putin to succeed".

title: Bangladesh and Myanmar 'preparing for the worst' ahead of cyclone
description: Tens of thousand of people living along the coast of Bangladesh and Myanmar have been urged to seek shelter as the nations brace for an extremely severe cyclone - known as Storm Mocha - on Sunday.

title: Who could be the next leader of Turkey? Polls open in pivotal elections
description: The polls for Turkey's presidential and parliamentary elections have opened after rallies on the last day of campaigning.
